The critical lines in the script relevant to the GNN structure for LP-graphs are from line 187 character 3 to line 349 character 10155.

The file also provides details about the numerical experiments conducted to validate the theoretical results. It mentions the generation of LP instances with specific values for m and n, and the use of scipy.optimize.linprog to obtain feasibility, optimal value, and optimal solution for each generated LP. It also describes the training of GNNs to fit the LP characteristics by minimizing the distance between GNN-output and solver-generated answers, using TensorFlow for implementation. Additionally, it specifies the parameterization of multi-linear perceptrons (MLPs) for learnable functions. However, the file does not provide specific details about the results of the numerical experiments.
```

